# Changelog

## [21] behavior-rules-dict-schema — 2026-03-06

**Why:** The LLM prompt compiler always returned `behavior_rules` as a structured dict with semantic keys (`opening`, `probing`, `adaptation`, `feedback`, `closing`), but the frontend typed it as `string[]` and rendered it with a numeric index list. The `CollapsibleSection` component had no concept of labeled sub-sections. The AI rewrite flow for `behavior_rules` expected a JSON array back from the backend, and `applyAiRewrite` parsed only arrays and plain strings.

**What:** Changed `AgentPromptSpec.behavior_rules` from `string[]` to `Record<string, string>`. Added a `DictSection` component that renders each key as a labeled subsection with its own textarea, displayed in canonical order (`opening → probing → adaptation → feedback → closing`). Added `updateDictItem` helper. Widened `applyAiRewrite` to handle a `'dict'` type that parses a JSON object response. Updated all `applyAiRewrite` call sites to pass an explicit `'string' | 'list' | 'dict'` type tag.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/api.ts` — `AgentPromptSpec.behavior_rules` changed from `string[]` to `Record<string, string>` with a clarifying comment (`// { opening, probing, adaptation, feedback, closing }`)
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — added `updateDictItem(key, field, value)` helper that merges a single dict key into the edited spec via spread; `applyAiRewrite` signature changed from `(key, isList: boolean, content)` to `(key, type: 'string' | 'list' | 'dict', content)` — `'dict'` path parses a JSON object and replaces the whole dict, silently no-ops on parse failure; all `applyAiRewrite` call sites updated (identity_and_persona: `'string'`, session_brief: `'string'`, behavior_rules: `'dict'`, guardrails: `'list'`); `CollapsibleSection` for `behavior_rules` replaced with new `DictSection` component that uses `onItemChange: (field, val)` instead of `(idx, val)`; `CollapsibleSection` for guardrails unchanged; added `DictSection` sub-component: renders keys in `BEHAVIOR_KEY_ORDER = ['opening', 'probing', 'adaptation', 'feedback', 'closing']` order (unknown extra keys appended after), each key shown as a `text-[10px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-400` label above a `rows=2` textarea; collapse/expand + AI button header matches `CollapsibleSection` layout

---

## [20] profile-load-sequencing — 2026-03-06

**Why:** After clearing all DB rows, two concurrent calls to `GET /api/v1/profile/me` (React StrictMode double-fires effects) raced to create both the profile and the agentspace. The agentspace fetch in `AgentSpaceContext` fired before the profile creation finished — since profile creation is also what triggers default agentspace creation, the fetch returned an empty list and the UI showed a spinner indefinitely. Additionally, if profile creation failed entirely, the agentspace fetch would still proceed with a null profile.

**What:** Added a `!profile` guard to `loadSpaces` so the agentspace fetch only fires once both `profileLoading === false` and `profile !== null`. Added `profile` to the `useCallback` dependency array so the fetch re-triggers as soon as the profile becomes available.

**Changes:**
- `src/context/AgentSpaceContext.tsx` — `loadSpaces` bails early if `profileLoading || !profile` (was `profileLoading` only); `profile` added to the `useCallback` dependency array alongside `session?.access_token` and `profileLoading`; ensures agentspace fetch never fires while profile is still being created, preventing a race between default agentspace creation and the spaces list fetch

---

## [19] agentspace-mobile-layout — 2026-03-05

**Why:** The AgentSpace page was built desktop-first with no responsive breakpoints. The agents table (7 fixed columns, ~530px minimum width) and records table (6 columns) overflowed on mobile viewports. The RunDetailPanel was fixed at 500px, covering the whole screen on phones. The header avatar was oversized relative to the icon buttons at small widths.

**What:** Added full mobile responsiveness across the AgentSpace page using a dual-render pattern (mobile card + hidden desktop table row) for both `AgentRow` and `RunRow`. Table headers are hidden below `md`. Toolbars reflow correctly. Panels go full-width on mobile. Avatar scales down responsively.

**Changes:**
- `src/pages/AgentSpace.tsx` — main content padding: `px-4 md:px-6 py-4 md:py-6`; agents toolbar "Create Training Agent" button: `w-full md:w-auto justify-center` so it goes full-width when wrapped on mobile; agent table header: `hidden md:grid`; `AgentRow`: dual-render — mobile card shows agent name + persona + status/language badges in row 1, action buttons (copy live, copy test, toggle, configure) + date in row 2 (`md:hidden`), existing 7-column grid row prefixed `hidden md:grid`; records table header: `hidden md:grid`; `RunRow`: dual-render — mobile card shows name + score in row 1, email + type badge + date in row 2, agent name in row 3 (`md:hidden`), existing 6-column grid row prefixed `hidden md:grid`; Export CSV button label: `hidden sm:inline` (icon stays visible on all sizes)
- `src/components/agentspace/AgentSpaceHeader.tsx` — outer padding `px-3 md:px-5`; "Vivalyn" brand text: `hidden sm:block`; "/" separator: `hidden sm:block` (icon remains at all sizes)
- `src/components/agentspace/RunDetailPanel.tsx` — detail panel width: `w-full md:w-[500px]`; transcript panel positioning updated from `lg:` to `md:` breakpoints (`md:right-[500px] md:w-[420px] md:z-40`) to match the detail panel's breakpoint
- `src/components/ui/UserAvatar.tsx` — `sm` size changed from `w-9 h-9 text-sm` to `w-7 h-7 sm:w-9 sm:h-9 text-xs sm:text-sm` so the header avatar scales down on mobile to match the visual weight of adjacent icon buttons

---

## [18] records-transcript-panel — 2026-03-05

**Why:** The inline transcript load appended all chat bubbles at the bottom of the detail panel, creating an extremely long scrollable column. The "Load Transcript" button added unnecessary friction since transcript is always needed.

**What:** Removed the inline transcript section from `RunDetailPanel`. Transcript now auto-fetches on mount via `useEffect`. A compact "View Transcript" row (with message count badge once loaded) opens a separate `TranscriptPanel` — on desktop (≥ `md`) it slides in to the left of the detail panel so both are visible simultaneously; on mobile it slides over the detail panel as a full-screen overlay. Fixed a runtime crash where structured transcript content objects (`{why, type, excerpt}`) were rendered directly as React children.

**Changes:**
- `backend/main_web_server/routes/run_records.py` — added `GET /api/v1/agentspaces/{agentspace_id}/runs/{run_id}`: JWT auth + agentspace membership check; fetches single run record with full `transcript` field; verifies the run's agent belongs to the requested agentspace before returning
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `fetchRunRecordById(token, agentspaceId, runId) -> RunRecord` (`GET /api/v1/agentspaces/{id}/runs/{runId}`, auth required); updated `RunRecord.transcript` content type from `string` to `string | Record<string, unknown>` to match actual DB payloads
- `src/components/agentspace/RunDetailPanel.tsx` — added `resolveContent()` helper that extracts a displayable string from structured content objects (checks `excerpt`, `text`, `content` keys before falling back to `JSON.stringify`); `TranscriptBubble` now calls `resolveContent(content)` instead of rendering `content` directly; removed `loadTranscript` button pattern; added `useEffect` that calls `fetchRunRecordById` on mount (auto-fetch, no user action required); replaced inline transcript section with a single "View Transcript" button row showing a spinner while loading, message count badge once loaded, or retry link on error; added `transcriptOpen` state; added `TranscriptPanel` sub-component (fixed positioned, `md:right-[500px] md:w-[420px] md:z-40`, slides over on mobile `z-50`, side-by-side on desktop); `TranscriptPanel` renders chat bubbles with user (right-aligned `bg-indigo-50`) and agent (left-aligned `bg-gray-100`) styles; rendered via `AnimatePresence` at root of `RunDetailPanel` return

---

## [17] records-detail-sidebar — 2026-03-05

**Why:** The Records tab showed sessions as table rows that expanded inline to reveal metric chips and a text summary. The experience was cramped, didn't support viewing transcripts, and buried the evaluation scores in a wall of chips with no visual hierarchy.

**What:** Replaced inline row expansion with a slide-in sidebar panel. Clicking any row opens `RunDetailPanel` from the right. The panel shows a pure-SVG radar chart for the 4 evaluation metrics, per-metric score chips (color-coded), summary, highlights, and areas to improve — all in a clean scrollable layout. A "View Transcript" entry point is included (implemented fully in [18]).

**Changes:**
- `backend/main_web_server/routes/run_records.py` — see [18] (same endpoint added)
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `fetchRunRecordById` (see [18]); added `fetchAgentspaceRuns` already in [16]
- `src/pages/AgentSpace.tsx` — removed `expandedId` state; added `selectedRun: RunRecord | null` state; `RunRow` simplified from expand-toggle to `onSelect` callback; selected row highlighted with `bg-indigo-50/40`; `AnimatePresence` block at end of `RecordsTab` renders semi-transparent backdrop (`fixed inset-0 bg-black/10 z-30`) + `RunDetailPanel` when `selectedRun` is set; imported `RunDetailPanel`
- `src/components/agentspace/RunDetailPanel.tsx` — **new**; pure-SVG `RadarChart` sub-component: N axes evenly spaced, 3 background rings at 33/66/100% scale, indigo-600 fill polygon at 12% opacity, axis labels outside rings (truncated to 14 chars); overall score display (`text-4xl font-semibold`); per-metric chips with `scoreColor()` helper (emerald ≥8, amber ≥6, red <5); Summary, Session Overview, Highlights (`CheckCircle` icons), Areas to Improve (`ArrowRight` icons) sections; transcript entry point (see [18] for full implementation); slides in with `x: "100%" → 0` Framer Motion animation; close button + backdrop click both call `onClose`

---

## [16] agentspace-dashboard-redo — 2026-03-03

**Why:** The dashboard had two UX problems: (1) A redundant "Personal AgentSpace / Admin" block below the header duplicated information already visible in the header switcher. (2) The agents were displayed in a card grid with no way to see run records — admins had no visibility into session history, scores, or test-vs-live breakdowns without leaving the dashboard.

**What:** Removed the redundant header row. Added a small admin indicator (`Shield` icon) inline in the `AgentSpaceSwitcher` button. Converted the agents card grid to a compact list format. Added a two-tab layout ("Agents" / "Records") where the Records tab is a full-featured run records table with search, sort, type filter (All / Live / Test), inline row expansion to show per-metric scores and feedback, and CSV export.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/AgentSpaceSwitcher.tsx` — added `Shield` from lucide-react; renders `<Shield className="w-3 h-3 text-indigo-400 shrink-0" />` inside the trigger button after the space name, visible only when `activeSpace?.role === 'admin'`
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `agent_name: string` and `is_test: boolean` to `RunRecord` interface; made `transcript` optional (`transcript?`) since the new agentspace-level endpoint omits it for payload efficiency; added `fetchAgentspaceRuns(accessToken, agentspaceId) -> RunRecord[]` (`GET /api/v1/agentspaces/{id}/runs`, auth required)
- `src/pages/AgentSpace.tsx` — full rewrite: removed redundant space-name + role `<motion.div>` block; added `DashTab = 'agents' | 'records'` type with pill tab bar (`bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-1 w-fit`); replaced `AgentCard` grid component with `AgentRow` list component (icon, name+language tag, persona, status badge, date, copy-live icon, copy-test icon, live toggle, configure icon — all in one `flex items-center` row); added `SortField`, `FilterType` types; added `SortIcon` helper component (outside render, accepts `field/sortField/sortDir` props); added `RecordsTab` component with search input, All/Live/Test filter pill buttons, sortable column headers (User, Agent, Date — click cycles asc/desc), `RunRow` component with `AnimatePresence` inline expand showing per-metric score chips, `transcript_summary`, and feedback bullets, "Export CSV" button (calls `exportCsv()` which builds a Blob and triggers download); `avgScore()` helper computes average of `evaluation_report.scoring` values; both data-fetching `useEffect`s restructured as inner async `load()` functions to avoid synchronous setState-in-effect lint errors

---

## [15] eval-tab-ux-simplification — 2026-03-03

**Why:** The Evaluation tab in the agent configure view had an awkward two-step flow: users typed a free-text criteria description into a textarea, clicked "Generate with AI" to produce metrics, then saw the results in a read-only preview card. This meant the AI output couldn't be edited without clearing and regenerating, and the "Describe criteria" textarea added unnecessary friction for users who already knew exactly which metrics they wanted.

**What:** Replaced the two-step flow with directly editable fields for metrics and eval prompt. Moved the AI generation capability to a small circular `Sparkles` button in the card header — the same pattern used by other section headers throughout the configure view. The AI button opens a compact popover where users type a brief criteria description; on submit it calls `generateEvaluationCriteria` and populates both editable fields, which can then be tweaked before saving.

**Changes:**
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — removed criteria `<textarea>` + description text + full-width "Generate with AI" button from `EvaluationTab`; removed read-only animated metrics preview card and "Clear" / "Save Metrics" buttons; replaced with: `EvalAiButton` sub-component (circular `w-7 h-7` sparkles button, opens `AnimatePresence` popover with "Describe what to evaluate" label + text input + submit + close, calls `generateEvaluationCriteria` on submit, populates parent state via `onGenerated` callback); `Metrics` card with editable badge list (each metric has an inline `X` remove button) + "Add a metric" input row (`Enter` or "Add" button); `Eval Prompt` card with directly editable `<textarea>` for `report_curator_prompt`; single "Save" button at the bottom persists `{ metrics: metricNames, report_curator_prompt: evalPrompt }` (or `null` if both empty) via `updateAgent`; state initialized directly from `initialMetrics` props

---

## [14] session-reporting-flow — 2026-03-02

**Why:** Four related problems needed fixing together: (1) The frontend closed the WebSocket immediately after `endSession()`, so the `session_report` message (sent by the backend after generating the evaluation) could never be received — the frontend polled a REST endpoint instead, which consistently returned 404 before generation finished. (2) Certain audio chunks from Inworld TTS had odd byte lengths, crashing `Int16Array` with `RangeError: byte length of Int16Array should be a multiple of 2`. (3) After session end, the UX was a jarring dark loading screen followed by an abrupt jump to `ReportScreen` — the design should show `EndedScreen` immediately, with a live spinner while the report generates and a "View Report" button once it arrives. (4) The error page used a `🔒` emoji which broke the UI design system, and the agent configure view had no way to edit evaluation metrics post-creation.

**What:** Added a `'reporting'` WebSocket phase to the session hook that keeps the connection open while the backend generates the report. Redesigned post-session page flow so `EndedScreen` appears instantly after call end. Fixed Int16Array crash. Replaced emoji with Lucide icon. Added Session/Evaluation tabs to the agent configure view with a full AI-powered metric editor.

**Changes:**
- `src/hooks/useAgentSession.ts` — added `'reporting'` to `SessionPhase` type; added `SessionReport` interface (`report: EvaluationReport | null`, `runId: string | null`) and `sessionReport` state; `endSession()` now stops mic + mic AudioContext only (WS stays open), sends `{"type":"end_session"}`, and sets phase to `'reporting'`; added `case 'session_report'` in WS message handler: sets `sessionReport`, transitions phase to `'ended'`, calls `cleanup()`; added safety `useEffect` — if phase stays `'reporting'` for >25s, force-transitions to `'ended'` (guards against backend failure); fixed `enqueueAudio()`: trims trailing odd byte from `rawBuffer` before `new Int16Array(buf)` to prevent `RangeError`; fixed `ws.onclose` handler: uses functional `setPhase` update so it reads the current phase correctly and doesn't reset a cleanly-ended session back to `'ended'` via incorrect branching
- `src/pages/AgentLive.tsx` — `ActiveSession` now renders `EndedScreen` (with `isGeneratingReport`) during the `'reporting'` phase instead of a dark full-screen spinner, so the session-ended card appears the moment the user hangs up; replaced `<span className="text-2xl">🔒</span>` with `<Lock className="w-6 h-6 text-gray-500" />` (lucide-react) on the error state; removed `'report-loading'` page state entirely; added `'report'` page state that renders `ReportScreen`; `handleEnded(turnCount, report)`: if `report.report` has `scoring` data → `setReportData(report.report)` and go to `'ended'`; if graceful end but no scoring (no evaluation configured) → go to `'ended'` directly; if `report === null` (abrupt disconnect) → set `isPollingReport = true` and go to `'ended'`; fallback poll `useEffect` runs only when `isPollingReport && pageState === 'ended'` — calls `fetchLatestRunRecord` up to 2 times with 3s gap, sets `reportData` if a scored record is found, always clears `isPollingReport` when done; `EndedScreen` receives `isGeneratingReport={isPollingReport}`, `reportAvailable={!!reportData}`, `onViewReport={() => setPageState('report')}`; `ReportScreen` rendered at `'report'` page state
- `src/components/agentlive/EndedScreen.tsx` — added optional props `isGeneratingReport?: boolean`, `reportAvailable?: boolean`, `onViewReport?: () => void`; renders `Loader2` spinner + "Generating your report…" text when `isGeneratingReport`; renders indigo "View Report" button with `FileText` icon when `reportAvailable`; default state (no evaluation) shows "Your conversation transcript has been saved." unchanged
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — added `Tab = 'session' | 'evaluation'` type with tab pill row below header (`inline-flex bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-1`, active tab `bg-white shadow-sm`); "Save Changes" button is only rendered when `activeTab === 'session'`; added `EvaluationTab` sub-component: criteria `<textarea>` with descriptive placeholder, "Generate with AI" button (calls `generateEvaluationCriteria(accessToken, {task_definition, users_raw_evaluation_criteria})`, `Sparkles` + `Loader2` icons); animated metrics preview card (metric tags in `indigo-50/indigo-100` pills + curator prompt text, `motion.div` fade-in on arrival); "Save Metrics" button calls `updateAgent(token, agentId, {transcript_evaluation_metrics: metrics})`; "Clear" link calls `updateAgent` with `transcript_evaluation_metrics: null`; empty dashed-border card when no metrics are configured; imported `generateEvaluationCriteria` from api
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `transcript_evaluation_metrics?: EvaluationMetrics | null` to `updateAgent` updates parameter type

---

## [13] evaluation-wizard-and-report-ui — 2026-03-02

**Why:** Agents could store `transcript_evaluation_metrics` in the DB, and the backend could generate and apply them, but there was no UI for setting them up during agent creation, no screen to display the resulting evaluation report after a session, and the API layer had no types or functions to support either operation.

**What:** Added the `EvaluationStep` to the agent creation wizard, built the full `ReportScreen` for post-session report display, and extended the API layer with evaluation types and functions.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `EvaluationMetrics` interface (`report_curator_prompt: string`, `metrics: string[]`); added `EvaluationReport` interface (`scoring: Record<string, number>`, `highlights: string[]`, `transcript_summary: string`, `feedback: string[]`, `summary: string`); added `RunRecord` interface (`id`, `created_at`, `agent_id`, `user_email`, `user_name`, `transcript`, `evaluation_report`); added `generateEvaluationCriteria(accessToken, {task_definition, users_raw_evaluation_criteria}) -> EvaluationMetrics` (`POST /api/v1/agents/generate-evaluation-criteria`); added `fetchLatestRunRecord(agentId, email) -> RunRecord | null` (`GET /api/v1/agents/{id}/runs/latest`, returns `null` on 404 or network error); added `transcript_evaluation_metrics?: EvaluationMetrics | null` to `Agent` interface and `saveAgent` payload type
- `src/components/agentspace/CreateAgentWizard.tsx` — added `'evaluation'` as a 6th wizard step after `'done'`; added `EvaluationStep` sub-component: `<textarea>` with Cmd+Enter shortcut to trigger generation, `Sparkles`-icon "Generate Metrics" primary button (disabled while empty or generating), animated metrics preview (`AnimatePresence` + `motion.div` fade-in) showing metric tags in `indigo-50` + curator prompt text, "Save & Continue" / "Skip & Save" button (label switches based on whether metrics were generated); parent `CreateAgentWizard` state additions: `evaluationCriteria: string`, `generatedMetrics: EvaluationMetrics | null`, `isGeneratingMetrics: boolean`, `isSavingAgent: boolean`; `handleGenerate()` calls `generateEvaluationCriteria()` using `compiled.task_definition` and the entered criteria; `handleSaveAgent()` calls `saveAgent()` with `transcript_evaluation_metrics: generatedMetrics ?? undefined`; fixed scroll blocking bug in `EvaluationStep` — root `div` is `flex flex-col h-full`, inner scroller is `flex-1 overflow-y-auto`, content centred with nested `min-h-full flex items-center justify-center` so it centres when content is short and scrolls when tall
- `src/components/agentlive/ReportScreen.tsx` — **new**; full post-session evaluation report display; `scoreColors(score: number)` helper returns Tailwind bg/border/text class strings and a label (`Excellent ≥9`, `Good ≥7`, `Fair ≥5`, `Needs work <5`); layout: header with agent name, user name, turn count, and average score chip; overall summary prose block; score heatmap grid (staggered `motion.div` cards, each showing numeric score, colour-coded label, and metric name); highlights list (emerald `CheckCircle2` bullets); feedback list (indigo `ArrowRight` bullets); transcript summary section

---

## [12] session-ui-and-persona-name — 2026-02-25

**Why:** Four gaps remained after agent-live-ui ([11]) and voice-ui-abstraction ([10]): (1) The live session screen only showed the agent avatar — users had no visual representation in the call, making it feel one-sided. (2) `AgentPublicConfig` didn't expose the agent's persona name (e.g. "Arjun"), so the session screen always displayed the raw `agent_name` instead of the configured persona. (3) The `AgentCard` deploy section was gated to admins only, but link sharing is useful to all space members. (4) `voiceConfig.ts` still exported WaveNet-specific helpers (`VOICE_NAMES`, `getVoiceName()`) that were meaningless after the Inworld migration since Inworld voices are already named strings.

**What:** Added a `UserAvatar` component to the live session screen and redesigned `SessionScreen` into a two-card side-by-side layout (agent + user). Extended `AgentPublicConfig` with `persona_name` and wired it through `AgentLive` so the session displays the persona name. Removed the admin gate from `AgentCard`'s deploy section. Cleaned up `voiceConfig.ts`. Updated `AgentConfigureView.tsx` VoiceBar to persist the Inworld voice name as `agent_prompt.name` (top-level persona field) instead of the old `voice_character` sub-object.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `persona_name?: string | null` to `AgentPublicConfig`; added `name: string` to `AgentPromptSpec` (top-level persona name, replaces the old `voice_character: {name}` sub-object pattern)
- `src/pages/AgentLive.tsx` — `ActiveSession` now passes `config?.persona_name ?? config?.agent_name` as `agentName` so the session screen uses the persona name; `SessionScreen` now also receives `userName` prop
- `src/components/agentlive/SessionScreen.tsx` — **redesigned**: two-card side-by-side layout (agent card + user card), each a frosted-glass `rounded-2xl border border-gray-700/60 bg-linear-to-b from-gray-800/70 to-gray-900/80 backdrop-blur-sm` panel; added `userName` prop; uses new `UserAvatar` component for user card; `isUserSpeaking` derived from `agentState === 'listening' && micEnabled`; user card subtitle shows "Speaking" / "Muted" / blank
- `src/components/agentlive/UserAvatar.tsx` — **new**; 144 px violet gradient circle with user initials (`getInitials()` handles multi-word names, max 2 chars); `isSpeaking`: two staggered emerald Framer Motion ripple rings (scale+opacity loop); `!micEnabled`: `MicOff` badge (bottom-right, `w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700`) + circle dims to `opacity-60`
- `src/pages/AgentSpace.tsx` — `AgentCard`: removed `userRole` prop; deploy section (Go Live toggle + Copy Live Link + Copy Test Link) is now visible to **all space members**, not admin-only; Configure button rendered as a always-visible full-width bordered button (`border-indigo-200 text-indigo-600`)
- `src/components/agentspace/CreateAgentWizard.tsx` — `runCompiler()` now includes `name: selectedPersonaName` in the `agent_prompt` payload on auto-save; `DoneStep` replaces the old "Done" action button with a disabled "Deploy" button carrying a "Soon" badge, encouraging users to Configure first
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/voiceConfig.ts` — removed `VOICE_NAMES` (WaveNet preference-to-persona-name map) and `getVoiceName()` helper; now only exports `FLAG_MAP` and `PREF_LABELS` — Inworld voice names are used directly as display names
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/AgentConfigureView.tsx` — `VoiceBar.handleUpdate()` now patches `agent_prompt: { ...editedSpec, name: personaName }` where `personaName = selectedVoiceName` (the Inworld voice name doubles as the persona name); `onUpdated` callback signature updated to `(lang, voice, personaName)`; `handleVoiceUpdated` in parent sets `edited.name = personaName` so the next "Save Changes" persists it; `displayPersona` shows `editedSpec.name ?? agentVoice`
- `src/components/agentspace/wizard/LanguageVoiceSelector.tsx` — voice cards now show `voice.voice_name` (Inworld name e.g. "Ashley") directly instead of `getVoiceName(...)` (which was WaveNet-specific)

---

## [11] agent-live-ui — 2026-02-23

**Why:** Agents could be configured and saved but had no way to be run by end-users. Admins needed a way to mark an agent live (or pause it) and share a direct link. External users needed a video-call-style interface to interact with a deployed agent via voice. Internal members needed a test link that bypasses the live/idle restriction so they can validate the agent before going live.

**What:** Added the complete agent live interaction layer: a public `/agent/:agentId` route with a video-call-style UI (animated agent avatar, real-time transcript panel, session controls), a `useAgentSession` hook managing WebSocket + mic + TTS audio, and AgentCard updates in the AgentSpace with Live/Idle status badge, Go Live toggle, and copy-link buttons.

**Changes:**
- `src/lib/api.ts` — added `agent_status: 'live' | 'idle'` to `Agent` interface; added `AgentPublicConfig` interface (`agent_name`, `agent_language`, `agent_status`); added `fetchAgentPublicConfig(agentId)` (no auth, `GET /api/v1/agents/{id}/public-config`); added `toggleAgentStatus(token, agentId, status)` (`PATCH /api/v1/agents/{id}/status`)
- `src/App.tsx` — added `/agent/:agentId` route pointing to `AgentLive` (no auth wrapper — public)
- `src/hooks/useAgentSession.ts` — **new**; manages full session lifecycle: WebSocket connection (`wss://.../ws/agent/{id}/session?email&name&mode&token`), mic capture (`AudioContext` 16kHz, `ScriptProcessorNode` bufferSize=1024, Float32→Int16 PCM binary frames), TTS playback (`AudioContext` 24kHz, gapless `BufferSource` scheduling via `nextPlayTimeRef`); state machine: `phase` (`connecting`→`active`→`ended`/`error`) + `agentState` (`listening`/`thinking`/`speaking`); React Strict Mode safe — uses `let mounted = true` per-effect guard so double-invoke in dev does not corrupt state; all handlers (`onmessage`, `onerror`, `onclose`) check `if (!mounted) return`; `session_ready` guards `ctx.resume()` with `state === 'suspended'` check and re-checks `mounted` after the `await`; `cleanup()` is idempotent (nulls all refs); `audio_done` polls `ctx.currentTime >= nextPlayTimeRef.current` to re-enable mic only after scheduled audio has finished; `sendAudioRef` stops mic sending during agent speaking to prevent echo; exposes `phase`, `agentState`, `transcript`, `micEnabled`, `toggleMic`, `endSession`, `error`
- `src/pages/AgentLive.tsx` — **new**; page state machine `loading → entry → session → ended / error`; loading: calls `fetchAgentPublicConfig`, blocks if live mode + `agent_status !== 'live'`; test mode: redirects to `/auth?next=/agent/${agentId}?mode=test` if no auth session; `ActiveSession` inner component mounts `useAgentSession` once join details are known — isolates hook from page-level re-renders; two-panel session layout: `SessionScreen` (flex-1) + `TranscriptPanel` (w-72 fixed RHS)
- `src/components/agentlive/AgentAvatar.tsx` — **new**; 120px circle with agent initials; `listening`: soft indigo pulse ring (Framer Motion scale+opacity loop); `thinking`: spinning dashed gray ring (`animate={{ rotate: 360 }}`); `speaking`: two expanding emerald rings with staggered delay
